  "body": "*Title*: Add a RBAC TCP filter\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nAdd a RBAC (Role-Based-Access-Control) TCP filter. This is needed to support authorization for non-HTTP protocol.\r\n\r\n*Relevant Links*:\r\nThe RBAC HTTP filter is added in #3455 \r\n\r\nsome open questions:\r\nWe could either add a new config proto for the TCP filter that includes fields only available in TCP or just reuse the existing [config proto](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/028387a3b0746deaf011ea50104692dfbb8b8d2f/api/envoy/config/rbac/v2alpha/rbac.proto#L48) introduced for HTTP filter, and only a subset of the fields are supported in this case.\r\nI prefer the second option but not sure if there is any preference in Envoy when a filter is implemented for both HTTP and TCP.\r\n\r\n\r\n/cc @liminw @lizan @rodaine @mattklein123 ",
